# AhaDiff Agent

Use AhaDiff after code changes to produce verified learn-back artifacts. OpenCode
can also pick up project skills from `.agents/skills` when the workspace uses
that shared convention.

Preferred commands:

- `ahadiff learn HEAD~1..HEAD`
- `ahadiff learn --staged`
- `ahadiff quiz <run_id>`
- `ahadiff review`
- `ahadiff verify <run_id>`
- `ahadiff improve <run_id>`
- `ahadiff serve`

Use verified claims and file-line evidence when explaining changes. Keep
`.ahadiff/review.sqlite`, `.ahadiff/runs/`, and `prompts/` local unless the repo
policy says otherwise. Do not commit local provider credentials, endpoints, or
private audit logs.
